item.title: 据表媒报道，马斯克将于周三参观德国千兆工厂
item.description: 据 Table Media 周二援引公司消息人士的话报道，埃隆-马斯克（Elon Musk）将于周三上午参观特斯拉位于德国的千兆工厂，上周附近的一座电力塔遭到纵火袭击，导致工厂停电并停止生产。【原文：Elon Musk will visit Tesla's gigafactory in Germany on Wednesday morning after an arson attack on a nearby power pylon last week left it without electricity and halted production, Table Media reported on Tuesday, citing company sources.】

item.title: 曼联第二季度盈利增长
item.description: 由于参加了本赛季利润丰厚的欧洲冠军联赛（UEFA Champions League）初期阶段的比赛，曼联第二季度的利润有所增长，但曼联周二仍维持其对 2024 年的预测不变。【原文：Manchester United kept its 2024 forecast unchanged on Tuesday after posting a rise in profit for the second quarter due to its participation in the early stages of the lucrative UEFA Champions League this season.】

item.title: 科尔百货假日季度销售额降幅低于预期
item.description: 科尔百货公司（Kohl's）周二公布的季度销售额降幅小于预期，这主要得益于其服装和鞋类产品的假日折扣，以及丝芙兰（Sephora）门店强劲的美容产品销售。【原文：Kohl's on Tuesday posted a smaller-than-expected drop in quarterly sales, helped by holiday discounts for its apparel and footwear as well as strong beauty sales at its Sephora stores.】

item.title: 渣打银行投资银行主管库珀将离职
item.description: 渣打银行周二表示，投资银行主管西蒙-库珀（Simon Cooper）将离职，作为管理层调整的一部分，罗伯托-霍恩韦格（Roberto Hoornweg）和苏尼尔-考沙尔（Sunil Kaushal）将接任企业与投资银行联席主管。【原文：Standard Chartered's head of investment banking Simon Cooper is to leave, the lender said on Tuesday as part of a management reshuffle that will see Roberto Hoornweg and Sunil Kaushal take over as co-heads of corporate and investment banking.】

item.title: 西南航空公司再次下调波音公司的喷气机交付预测
item.description: 美国西南航空公司周二再次下调了对供应商波音公司飞机交付数量的预期，导致这家美国国内最大的航空公司削减了 2024 年下半年的运力。【原文：Southwest Airlines on Tuesday once again cut its forecast for the number of aircraft deliveries it expects from supplier Boeing - causing the largest domestic U.S. carrier to cut its capacity for the second half of 2024.】

item.title: 甲骨文大涨，人工智能需求助力云业务重燃动力
item.description: 周二，甲骨文飙升13%，原因是有迹象表明，由于与人工智能芯片巨头英伟达（Nvidia）的合作，该公司抢占云计算市场份额的计划正在取得进展。【原文：Oracle soared 13% on Tuesday, on signs the firm was making progress in its plan to grab a share of the cloud-computing market thanks to its tie-up with AI chip giant Nvidia.】

item.title: 3M 将任命威廉-布朗为首席执行官
item.description: 工业集团 3M 周二表示，将任命威廉-布朗（William Brown）为首席执行官，5 月 1 日起生效。【原文：Industrial conglomerate 3M on Tuesday said that William Brown will be appointed as chief executive officer, effective May 1.】

item.title: 达美航空公司重申第一季度盈利预期
item.description: 达美航空公司（Delta Air Lines）周二重申了第一季度的盈利预期，原因是国际旅游需求保持强劲。【原文：Delta Air Lines reaffirmed its first-quarter profit forecast on Tuesday on resilient international travel demand.】

item.title: 阿拉斯加航空公司预计亏损幅度低于预期
item.description: 阿拉斯加航空集团（Alaska Air Group）周二预测，由于旅游需求强劲，第一季度亏损将小于预期。【原文：Alaska Air Group , the operator of the 737 MAX 9 jet that experienced a mid-air cabin panel blowout, forecast a narrower-than-expected first-quarter loss on Tuesday due to strong travel demand.】

item.title: ADM 在会计实务调查中更正财务报表
item.description: 全球谷物商 Archer-Daniels-Midland 周二更正了之前的部分财务报表。【原文：Global grains merchant Archer-Daniels-Midland corrected parts of previous financial statements on Tuesday.】

item.title: 对冲基金提高杠杆率，接近历史最高水平，以提高回报率
item.description: 据两位银行业消息人士和各大银行最近的客户说明称，近年来，以债务为动力的策略急剧膨胀，而金融市场的回暖又促使对冲基金进行更高风险的押注，因此对冲基金在股票交易中使用的杠杆接近创纪录水平。【原文：Hedge funds' use of leverage in equities trading is near record levels after debt-fueled strategies ballooned in recent years and an upturn in financial markets prompted riskier bets, according to two banking sources and recent client notes from major banks.】

item.title: 总部位于美国的 CarbonCapture 公司从沙特阿美石油公司等机构融资 8000 万美元
item.description: 总部位于洛杉矶的碳捕捉公司（CarbonCapture）旨在制造能从空气中吸走二氧化碳以应对气候变化的机器，该公司称已从包括沙特石油巨头沙特阿美在内的投资者那里筹集到 8000 万美元。【原文：Los Angeles-based CarbonCapture, which aims to build machines that suck carbon dioxide out of the air to fight climate change, said it had raised $80 million from investors that include Saudi oil giant Saudi Aramco .】

item.title: 美国小型企业协会（NFIB）称，美国小型企业乐观情绪降至 9 个月来最低点
item.description: 本周二公布的一份报告显示，由于对通胀的持续担忧，美国小型企业的景气度在 2 月份降至 5 月份以来的最低水平。【原文：U.S. small business sentiment fell in February to the lowest level since May due to continued concerns around inflation, according to a report published on Tuesday.】

item.title: 早间竞标：市场仪表盘上的通胀温度计
item.description: Mike Dolan 展望美国和全球市场的未来一天【原文：A look at the day ahead in U.S. and global markets from Mike Dolan】

item.title: 消息人士称，英特尔在停止向中国华为销售数百万美元产品的申请中幸存下来
item.description: 两位熟知内情的人士称，英特尔已成功阻止了向华为销售价值数亿美元芯片的努力，这使得全球最大的芯片制造商之一有更多时间向这家受到严厉制裁的中国电信公司销售芯片。【原文：Intel has survived an effort to halt hundreds of millions of dollars' worth of chip sales to Huawei, two people familiar with the matter said, giving one of the world's largest chipmakers more time to sell to the heavily sanctioned Chinese telecoms company.】

item.title: 独家报道高盛寻求在五年内将私人信贷组合规模扩大至 3,000 亿美元
item.description: 高盛集团（Goldman Sachs Group）旗下高盛资产管理公司（Goldman Sachs Asset Management）的一位高级管理人员表示，该公司的目标是在五年内将其私人信贷投资组合从目前的 1,300 亿美元扩大到 3,000 亿美元，并制定了一项积极的扩张计划。【原文：Goldman Sachs Asset Management, a unit of Goldman Sachs Group , aims to expand its private credit portfolio to $300 billion in five years from the current $130 billion, a senior executive said, laying out an aggressive expansion plan.】

item.title: 据《每日邮报》报道，卡车制造商沃尔沃放慢生产速度并裁员 250 人
item.description: 据当地日报《哥德堡邮报》（Goteborgs-Posten）周二援引公司发言人的话报道，瑞典卡车制造商沃尔沃公司（AB Volvo）计划放慢哥德堡图维（Tuve）工厂的生产速度，并裁员250人。【原文：Swedish truck maker AB Volvo plans to slow down the pace of production at its Tuve plant in Gothenburg and cut 250 jobs at the facility, local daily Goteborgs-Posten reported on Tuesday, citing a company spokesperson.】

item.title: 中国江淮汽车与大众汽车（中国）将加大对合资公司的投资力度
item.description: 中国安徽江淮汽车周二表示，该公司和大众中国将把合资企业的注册资本从 74 亿元增至 139 亿元。【原文：China's Anhui Jianghuai Automobile said on Tuesday it and Volkswagen China will boost their joint venture's registered capital to 13.9 billion yuan from 7.4 billion yuan.】

item.title: 标准普尔 500 指数和纳斯达克指数期货在关键通胀测试前走高
item.description: 周二，在美国消费者物价数据公布之前，美国 500 指数和纳斯达克指数期货均有所上涨，这些数据可能会让人洞察到通胀是否已经缓解到足以让美联储在未来几个月降低借贷成本的程度。【原文：S&P 500 and Nasdaq futures inched up on Tuesday ahead of U.S. consumer prices data that could provide insight on whether inflation has eased enough for the Federal Reserve to lower borrowing costs in coming months.】

item.title: 人工智能进入 "良性循环"，美银美林上调标普 500 指数 2024 年盈利预期
item.description: 博雅全球研究公司（BofA Global Research）周二上调了对 S&P 500 指数的盈利预测，预计该基准指数中的公司今年利润将增长 12%。【原文：BofA Global Research raised its earnings forecast for the S&P 500 on Tuesday, projecting a 12% increase in profit for the companies in the benchmark index this year.】

item.title: 德国 Westenergie 公司表示，特斯拉案例表明电网需要关注
item.description: 德国一家重量级电网公司的母公司--Westenergie 的负责人表示，德国决策者应与电网运营商合作，加强应对特斯拉柏林附近千兆工厂附近发生的纵火袭击等事件。【原文：German policymakers should come on board with grid operators to step up responses to incidents such as the arson attack near Tesla's gigafactory near Berlin, said the head of Germany's Westenergie , parent to a weighty grid firm.】

item.title: 消息人士称，日本央行将在结束YCC后就债券购买步伐提供指引
item.description: 四位熟悉日本央行想法的消息人士称，日本央行可能会就结束负利率和收益率曲线控制（YCC）后将购买多少政府债券提供数字指导，以避免造成市场混乱。【原文：The Bank of Japan will likely offer numerical guidance on how much government bonds it will buy upon ending negative interest rates and yield curve control (YCC), to avoid causing market disruptions, said four sources familiar with its thinking.】

item.title: 大多数韩国央行董事会成员认为政策转向为时尚早 - 会议纪要
item.description: 周二的会议纪要显示，在2月22日举行的利率决策会议上，大多数韩国央行董事会成员都表示，现在调整货币政策还为时过早，因为决策者仍将稳定物价放在首位。【原文：Most Bank of Korea board members said it was too early for a pivot in monetary policy at their rate decision meeting on Feb. 22, minutes showed on Tuesday, as policymakers continued to prioritise stabilising prices.】

item.title: 多米诺比萨集团因成本缓解而利润增加
item.description: 英国多米诺比萨集团（Domino's Pizza Group）周二发布报告称，受原材料成本下降的支撑，该集团 2023 年的利润将略有增长，并预计本年度的利润将符合预期。【原文：Britain's Domino's Pizza Group on Tuesday reported a marginal rise in its 2023 profit, and also forecast profit for the current year to be in line with expectations, supported by the easing of raw material costs.】

item.title: 独家报道中国总理李克强将不出席重要商业峰会与全球首席执行官会面
item.description: 三位知情人士透露，中国国务院总理李强不打算在即将于 3 月下旬举行的中国发展高层论坛（CDF）上与来访的外国首席执行官会面。【原文：Chinese Premier Li Qiang does not intend to hold a meeting with visiting foreign CEOs at the upcoming China Development Forum (CDF) in late March, three sources briefed on the matter said, raising concerns about Beijing's commitment to attract investment from abroad at a time of souring sentiment.】

item.title: 保时捷预计 2024 年回报率将随着新车型的推出而降低
item.description: 德国豪华汽车制造商保时捷周二表示，尽管市场波动较大，但该公司发布的全年业绩基本符合预期。【原文：German luxury carmaker Porsche expects profitability to tick downwards in 2024 as it focuses on launching four new models, the company said on Tuesday, posting full-year results largely in line with expectations despite market volatility.】

item.title: 特斯拉称德国工厂全面恢复生产尚需时日
item.description: 特斯拉位于柏林附近的德国千兆工厂负责人安德烈-蒂埃里希（Andre Thierig）周一晚些时候表示，该工厂还需要一段时间才能完全恢复生产。【原文：It will take some time until production at Tesla's German gigafactory near Berlin will fully resume, plant head Andre Thierig said late on Monday.】

item.title: 独家报道消息称中国体操冠军李宁考虑将公司私有化
item.description: 中国亿万富翁、奥运冠军李宁正在考虑将其同名运动服装公司从香港证券交易所私有化。【原文：Chinese billionaire entrepreneur and Olympic champion Li Ning is considering taking his namesake sportswear company private from the Hong Kong stock exchange, four people said, adding to a string of such potential deals in a faltering market.】

item.title: 欧洲 英镑多头为英国工资测试做好准备
item.description: 安库尔-班纳吉（Ankur Banerjee）对欧洲和全球市场未来一天的展望【原文：A look at the day ahead in European and global markets from Ankur Banerjee】

item.title: 据彭博新闻社报道，加拿大国家银行考虑出售柬埔寨分行
item.description: 据彭博社周二援引知情人士的话报道，加拿大国民银行正在为其柬埔寨分行 ABA Bank 寻求各种选择，包括以超过 20 亿美元的价格出售该银行。【原文：National Bank of Canada is exploring options for its Cambodian unit ABA Bank, including its sale for more than $2 billion in a deal, Bloomberg reported on Tuesday, citing people familiar with the matter.】
